1 Visualization 1: Exercise solutions

1.1 Load packages and set theme

Let’s first load the packages that we need for this chapter.

library("knitr")     # for rendering the RMarkdown file
library("tidyverse") # for data wrangling

Let’s set the plotting theme.

theme_set(theme_classic() + #set the theme 
    theme(text = element_text(size = 20))) #set the default text size

1.2 Practice plot 1

Recreate the plot shown in Figure 1.2.

ggplot(data = diamonds,
       mapping = aes(x = depth,
                     y = table)) +
  geom_point()

Figure 1.1: Practice plot 1. 

include_graphics("figures/practice_plot1.png")

Figure 1.2: Practice plot 1.

Recreate the plot shown in Figure 1.4.

ggplot(data = diamonds,
       mapping = aes(x = depth,
                     y = table)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.1) + 
  labs(x = "Depth (in mm)",
       y = "Table\n(width of top of diamond relative to widest point)")

1.3 Practice plot 2

Recreate the plot shown in Figure 1.5.

ggplot(data = diamonds,
       mapping = aes(x = clarity,
                     y = price)) +
  stat_summary(fun = "mean",
               geom = "bar") +
  stat_summary(fun.data = "mean_cl_boot",
               geom = "linerange")

include_graphics("figures/practice_plot2.png")

Figure 1.5: Practice plot 2.

Recreate the plot shown in Figure 1.6.

ggplot(data = diamonds,
       mapping = aes(x = clarity,
                     y = price)) +
  stat_summary(fun = "mean",
               geom = "bar",
               color = "black",
               fill = "lightblue") +
  stat_summary(fun.data = "mean_cl_boot",
               geom = "linerange",
               size = 1) +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.1)))

Figure 1.6: Practice plot 2 (advanced).

1.4 Practice plot 3

Recreate the plot shown in Figure 1.7.

ggplot(data = diamonds, 
       mapping = aes(x = color,
                     y = price,
                     group = clarity,
                     color = clarity)) +
  stat_summary(fun.data = "mean_cl_boot",
               geom = "pointrange",
               size = 1) + 
  stat_summary(fun = "mean",
               geom = "line",
               size = 2)

Figure 1.7: Practice plot 3.

Recreate the plot shown in Figure 1.8.

ggplot(data = diamonds, 
       mapping = aes(x = color,
                     y = price,
                     group = clarity,
                     color = clarity)) +
  stat_summary(fun = "mean",
               geom = "line",
               size = 2,
               position = position_dodge(width = 0.9)) + 
  stat_summary(fun.data = "mean_cl_boot",
               geom = "pointrange",
               shape = 21, 
               fill = "white",
               size = 1,
               position = position_dodge(width = 0.9)) + 
  geom_vline(xintercept = seq(from = 1.5,
                              by = 1,
                              length.out = 6),
             linetype = 2,
             color = "gray20")

Figure 1.8: Practice plot 3 (advanced).

1.5 Practice plot 4

Recreate the plot shown in Figure 1.9.

ggplot(data = diamonds,
       mapping = aes(x = color,
                     y = price,
                     fill = cut)) +
  stat_summary(fun = "mean",
               geom = "bar",
               position = position_dodge(width = 0.9),
               color = "black") +
  stat_summary(fun.data = "mean_cl_boot",
               geom = "linerange",
               position = position_dodge(width = 0.9),
               color = "black") +
  facet_grid(rows = vars(clarity)) +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(size = 8),
        strip.text = element_text(size = 10))

Figure 1.9: Practice plot 4.
